# OneStreamer CODEOWNERS
#
# When a PR touches files matching a pattern below, the corresponding owner(s)
# are automatically requested for review.
#
# Patterns are evaluated bottom-to-top; the last matching pattern wins.

# Default owner for everything
* @<your-github-handle>

# Examples for when the team grows — uncomment and adjust:
#
# /server/                  @<backend-lead>
# /client/                  @<frontend-lead>
# /chat-service/            @<backend-lead>
# /docs/                    @<docs-owner>
# /docs/architecture/adr/   @<architecture-reviewer>
# /docs/security/           @<security-reviewer>
# /docs/operations/         @<operator>
# *.yml                     @<devops-lead>
# /.github/                 @<devops-lead>
# /ecosystem.config.js      @<devops-lead>

# TODO: replace `@<your-github-handle>` above with the actual GitHub handle
# of the repository owner. Without this, GitHub will not auto-request
# reviewers and the CODEOWNERS file silently has no effect.
